% ====================================================================
% test_bestagon_combat_core.trx -- run examples/bestagon-sim/combat-core
% self-test via the standard tests/ harness.
% ====================================================================
%
% Thin wrapper: loads examples/bestagon-sim/combat-core.trx (the shared
% combat resolver, Phase 0.5A), then explicitly invokes run-self-test.
% combat-core's own dispatch-cli is a no-op when invoked without
% --self-test (the flag is only seen when combat-core is the script
% directly executed by ./trix).
%
% Asserts:
%   - §9.3 worked example reproduces byte-for-byte (5 HP / 2 HP /
%     0.84 stars / 0.756 stars)
%   - vet thresholds (0/3/5/8 -> 0/1/2/3)
%   - sparse damage-table lookup (defined + missing branches)
%   - all 6 CO classification + 6 unit class predicates
%   - all 6x6 CO matchup smoke (Tank-vs-Tank Plain)
%   - illegal attacks raise /undefined
%   - weather and veterancy fold through the resolver correctly
% ====================================================================

(examples/bestagon-sim/combat-core.trx) run
run-self-test
(__test_ok__) =
